%N A202093 Number of (n+2) X 3 binary arrays avoiding patterns 001 and 011 in rows and columns.
%C A202093 Part of a family of width-w binary arrays avoiding 001 and 011 (w=3..9: A202093-A202099) with common formula a(n) = C(alpha+E,E)*C(alpha+O,O)*C(beta+E,E)*C(beta+O,O) where E=ceil(w/2), O=floor(w/2), alpha=floor((n+3)/2), beta=floor((n+2)/2). - _Christian Krause_, Jun 26 2026
%H A202093 R. H. Hardin, <a href="/A202093/b202093.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..210</a>
%H A202093 Christian Krause, <a href="/A202093/a202093.txt">Proof of formula</a>, Jun 26 2026
%H A202093 <a href="/index/Rec#order_12">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (2,4,-10,-5,20,0,-20,5,10,-4,-2,1).
%F A202093 a(n) = 2*a(n-1) +4*a(n-2) -10*a(n-3) -5*a(n-4) +20*a(n-5) -20*a(n-7) +5*a(n-8) +10*a(n-9) -4*a(n-10) -2*a(n-11) +a(n-12). [proved by _Christian Krause_, Jun 26 2026]
%F A202093 From _Colin Barker_, Feb 20 2018: (Start)
%F A202093 G.f.: x*(108 + 108*x - 360*x^2 - 56*x^3 + 700*x^4 - 115*x^5 - 680*x^6 + 236*x^7 + 334*x^8 - 155*x^9 - 66*x^10 + 36*x^11) / ((1 - x)^7*(1 + x)^5).
%F A202093 a(n) = (n^6 + 28*n^5 + 324*n^4 + 1984*n^3 + 6784*n^2 + 12288*n + 9216) / 256 for n even.
%F A202093 a(n) = (n^6 + 28*n^5 + 321*n^4 + 1928*n^3 + 6395*n^2 + 11100*n + 7875) / 256 for n odd.
%F A202093 (End) [proved by _Christian Krause_, Jun 26 2026]
%F A202093 From _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 28 2026: (Start)
%F A202093 Sum_{n>=1} 1/a(n) = 2*Pi^4/45 + 11*Pi^2/3 - 4*zeta(3) - 1285/36.
%F A202093 Sum_{n>=1} (-1)^(n+1)/a(n) = 12*zeta(3) + 229/36 - 2*Pi^4/45 - 5*Pi^2/3. (End)
